[thinking] **Evaluating JDK compatibility**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm noticing that with JDK17 and above, strong encapsulation is denying illegal access. The default behavior for OGNL pre-JDK9 allows setAccessible, but it can fail for java.base internals. Currently, the existing build is using "add-opens" for java.lang. I wonder if it's possible to conduct meaningful tests without relying on JDK internals. Also, there's a thought that OgnlOps may attempt to access "class.name." Hmm, there’s a lot to consider here!
[thinking] 
