idance\": \"If tests intentionally exercise deep reflection against JDK classes or OGNL's JDK9+ access-handler paths, they may need JVM test args such as --add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED, matching the existing OGNL 3.2.21 test project. Do not enable OGNL security-manager properties unless a test specifically targets that feature, because SecurityManager behavior is JDK-version-sensitive.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported failure is on JDK 25, where SecurityManager-related tests may be fragile or obsolete; that is test design/version compatibility rather than missing deterministic setup.\",\n    \"Javassist is required by OGNL's expression compiler, but it is a normal transitive dependency of ognl:ognl:3.3.5, so adding it explicitly should not be necessary unless Gradle/metadata resolution proves otherwise.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_084459f71f36e04a016a3f2a83400081908bf9d680efda19f1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3566, "output": 799, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33549, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782524533813, "responseId": "resp_084459f71f36e04a016a3f2a764ae081909f7bc385375ba26c"}}
